Lights out in Bahrain is exactly one week away with Max Verstappen hoping to defend his F1 world title and Lewis Hamilton aiming to spoil the party. The Brit may have his work cut out, however, after Mercedes' suboptimal three days of testing around the Bahrain International Circuit. With just a three-day test to hone their respective machines for the upcoming season, teams almost totted up a combined 4,000 laps in the Middle East as Red Bull once again established themselves as the class of the field. Much like they did last year, Mercedes underwhelmed with their lap times, which has drawn questions from rivals as to whether they could be concealing their true performance. Hamilton and team-mate George Russell took a realistic approach when reflecting on the past few days. With the season edging closer and noise around the sport's biggest names increasing, follow Express Sport's live updates below as we pledge to keep you informed throughout the day... DON'T MISS: Lewis Hamilton fears F1 bosses putting lives at risk with new FIA rule